# [TEAS](../wg/teas.html)

## Summary
The Traffic Engineering Architecture and Signaling (TEAS) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss the status of its active drafts, advance several key specifications toward Working Group Last Call (WGLC), and debate architectural extensions for service assurance, network slicing, and inter-operator coordination. 

Key advancements include preparing several Network Resource Partition (NRP) and RSVP-TE drafts for WGLC, addressing 3GPP liaison feedback for network slice applications, and proposing a scoping reduction for Abstraction and Control of Traffic Engineered Networks (ACTN) Packet Optical Integration (POI) service assurance.

